cs.ET, cs.NE, cs.BI, cs.SY, cs.RO 

The paper proposes a new approach to computing using cytoskeleton networks, which involves programmable polymerization and collision-based logical gates. This falls under the category of "emerging technologies" (cs.ET) in computer science. Additionally, the use of solitons and conformational defects for data signals suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and bioinformatics (cs.BI). The implementation of the computation via collisions at structural gates also involves a systems approach (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO) in terms of designing and controlling the cytoskeleton networks.
